'''Saleh Khalid Mohammed Al-Shehri''' ({{langx|ar|صالح خالد محمد الشهري}}; born on 1 November 1993) is a Saudi Arabian professional [[association football|football]] player who plays as a [[Striker (association football)|striker]] for [[Al-Ittihad Club (Jeddah)|Al-Ittihad]]<ref>{{Cite web |title=نمر جديد وصل |url=https://x.com/ittihad/status/1815371927810122177 |website=X}}</ref> and the [[Saudi Arabia national football team|Saudi Arabia national team]].

==Club career==
===Early career===
Saleh is a graduate of the Academy of [[Al-Ahli (Jeddah)|Al-Ahli]] and played as a striker in the ranks of Al-Ahli junior and youth.{{Citation needed|date=December 2021}}

===Beira-Mar===
Saleh made his debut on 2 September 2012 at [[S.C. Beira-Mar|Beira-Mar]] against [[Moreirense F.C.|Moreirense]] and scored the first goal in his first match. Saleh is the first Saudi Arabian to score in Europe.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://sabq.org/6fnfde |title=الشهري يسجِّل أول هدف سعودي في أوروبا |work=sabq.org |access-date=14 September 2012 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120916233415/http://sabq.org/6Fnfde |archive-date=16 September 2012}}</ref> At his second match against [[Vitória S.C.|Vitória]], he scored the fastest goal in [[Primeira Liga]] 12–13. Saleh played two matches and scored two goals with [[S.C. Beira-Mar]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://alarabiya.net/articles/2012/11/24/251567.html |title=السعودي الشهري يسجل أسرع هدف في الدوري البرتغالي|date=24 November 2012 |language=ar}}</ref>

===Return to Al-Ahli===
On 20 July 2013, Saleh returned to his club. He made his debut [[friendly match]] against [[Najran SC|Najran]] and losing the match score 1–0.{{Citation needed|date=December 2021}}

===Al-Ittihad===
On 22 July 2024, Al-Shehri joined [[Al-Ittihad Club (Jeddah)|Al-Ittihad]] on a free transfer.<ref>{{cite web |title=رسميًا.. الاتحاد يعلن التعاقد مع صالح الشهري |url=https://hihi2.com/2024/07/22/p2759023.html}}</ref>

==International career==

=== Youth ===
Saleh scored a goal against [[Qatar national under-20 football team|Qatar national under-20 team]] in the [[2012 AFC U-19 Championship]], with Saudi Arabia winning 4–2.{{Citation needed|date=December 2021}} Saudi Arabia collected four points, but were eliminated after finishing third.{{Citation needed|date=December 2021}}

=== Senior ===
On 22 November 2022, Saleh scored the first goal for [[Saudi Arabia national football team|Saudi Arabia]] against [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]] at the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] held in Qatar.<ref>{{Cite news |date=2022-11-22 |title=Soccer-Saudi Arabia shock Messi's Argentina with comeback victory |language=en |work=Reuters |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/soccer-worldcup-arg-sau-report-idCAKBN2SC0PE |access-date=2022-11-24}}</ref>

